. So what I gather is that xcodebuild just launches the simulator first, and then queries the test bundle. Querying the test bundle causes Specta to execute any code not inside a before, after, or it block.

To answer the question, yep, I set up a CoreData stack in my appDelegate for my test host, and because the app delegate was never called, the stack was never setup which leads to an assert. For me, the problem was easily solved by just moving some setup code into before blocks.

